Hey Ishmael,
Need to fill you in on what’s happening with the Mowry project.
The clients are refusing to pay for the completed framing milestone.
We finished the demo, foundation, slab, all framing, exterior siding,
and roofing - which triggers the first 40% payment per our contract.
They’ve only paid $39,650 and owe $42,420 at this point. They’re
now saying they won’t pay anything more until the entire project is
done, which isn’t how our contract works.
I sent them a formal legal notice this morning with a Stop Work Order
and 3-Day Payment Demand for $11,700. All work is paused until
they pay.
The electrician is coming today to get measurements and do his quote,
but no actual work. Can you meet him there to let him in and help him
get what he needs? Just measurements - no installation yet.
Important: Don’t mention any of this payment stuff to the electrician.
We’re not trying to scare our subs off the project. I just told him
there’s a brief payment hold and he’s good to quote. Keep it light with
him - just help him get his measurements and that’s it.
If the Mowrys are there and say anything to you, keep it simple:
you’re there to meet the electrician for measurements, work is paused
while we resolve a payment issue, that’s it. Don’t get into details or
arguments with them.
These folks are being difficult so we need to stay professional and let
the legal process work. Hopefully they pay within the 3 days and we
can get back to work.
Let me know when you’re headed over there.
