we can’t get ahold of the landscaper, here’s what we need to do: That
irrigation pipe and control wire cannot stay in the footing trench.
Option 1 (best): Reroute the irrigation line and wire around the footing
line and reconnect with couplers and waterproof splices.
Option 2 (if reroute isn’t possible): Cut the line, install a 2″+ PVC
sleeve across the trench (extending 6″ past both sides), and run both
the pipe and wire through the sleeve. Seal the ends so no concrete gets
in.
